 the Transmission Service Study ... 30 \n2.6. Award of Incremental TCCs ... 30 \n3. INTERCONNECTION PROCESS ... 31 \n3.1. Introduction31 \n3.2. What is an Interconnection? ... 32 \n3.3. Large Facility Interconnection Procedures (LFIP) ... 32 \n3.3.1. Basic Information about the LFIP ... 32 \n3.3.2. Large Facility Interconnection Request ... 37 \n3.3.3. Basic Steps of the LFIP ... 37 \n3.3.4. Materiality Determinations ... 57 \n3.4. Small Generator Interconnection Procedures (SGIP) ... 63 \n3.4.1. Basic Information about the SGIP ... 63 \n3.4.2. Small Generator Interconnection Request ... 66 \n3.4.3. Basic Steps of the SGIP ... 67 \n3.4.4. Small Generator Interconnection Studies ... 67 \n3.4.5. Small Generator Interconnection Agreement ... 68 \n3.4.6. Construction, Installation, Registration, and Operation ... 68 \n3.4.7. Modification of the Interconnection Request ... 69 \n3.5. Load Interconnection Procedures ... 69 \n3.6. Interconnection Study Methodology ... 70 \n\nDRAFT PURPOSES ONLY Transmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | iv\n\n3.6.1. Minimum Interconnection Standard Technical Assumptions ... 70 \n3.6.2. Cost Allocation Procedures (Pursuant to Class Year 2001 Settlement Agreement) ... 71 \nThese Cost Allocation Procedures implement the terms of a FERC settlement ... 72 \n3.6.3. Modeling of Dual Yard Units at the Astoria East and West 138 kV Station in Interconnection \nStudies ... 80 \n3.6.4. Deliverability Study Methodology ... 81 \n3.7. Inter-ISO Interconnection Procedures ... 89 \n4. TRANSMISSION PLANNING CRITERIA AND GUIDELINES ... 91 \n4.1. Introduction \n4.2. Applicable Reliability Criteria and Standards ... 91 \n4.3. NYISO Transmission Planning Guidelines ... 92 \nATTACHMENT A JURISDICTIONAL FLOW CHART ... 0 \nATTACHMENT B GENERAL FORM OF NYISO STUDY AGREEMENT ... 3 \nATTACHMENT C ACQUISITION OF CRIS RIGHTS ... 0 \nATTACHMENT D STEPS IN THE NYISO LARGE FACILITY INTERCONNECTION PROCESS ... 2 \nATTACHMENT E STEPS IN THE NYISO SMALL GENERATOR INTERCONNECTION PROCESS ... 11 \nATTACHMENT F NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #1-1 ... 18 \nATTACHMENT G NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #2-1 ... 22 \nATTACHMENT H NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #3-1 ... 25 \nATTACHMENT I NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #4-1 ... 31 \nATTACHMENT J NYISO TRANSMISSION PLANNING GUIDELINE #5-0 ... 36 \nATTACHMENT K COST ALLOCATION PROCEDURES PURSUANT CLASS YEAR 2001 SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT ... 38 \nATTACHMENT L NORMAL ISO OPERATING PROCEDURES ... 45 \n\nDRAFT PURPOSES ONLY Transmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | v\n\nTable of Figures \nFigure 1: Deposits Associated with the NYISO TIP ... 6 \nFigure 2: Sections of the NYISO OATT Related to the Interconnection Process ... 31 \nFigure 3: Deposits Associated with the NYISO LFIP ... 35 \nFigure 4: Exporting and Importing Regions for Highways ... 84 \nFigure 5: Exporting and Importing Regions for Other Interfaces ... 85 \nFigure 6: Review of Cases to Evaluate Transfer ... 88 \nFigure 7: Exhibit I - Voltage-Limited Power Transfer ... 24 \n\nDRAFT PURPOSES ONLY Transmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | vi\n\nRevision History\n\nVersion Date Revisions \n1.0 09/01/1999 Initial Release \n2.0 11/01/2012 Significant update and rewrite \n2.1 10/30/2015 Additional updates are being made to this manual, including \nupdates to reflect revisions to Attachments S, X and Z to the NYISO \nOATT effective February 18, 2013 (FERC Docket Nos. ER13-588- \n001 & ER13-588-002) and revisions to Attachments X and Z \neffective February 14, 2014 (FERC Docket No. ER14-627-000) \nGlobal \n Reformatted per new template to standardize presentation \n Standardized labeling and numbering of graphical and tabular \nmaterial \nSection 2.4.2 \n Update the MW threshold for Requiring a Transmission System \nImpact Study (SIS) \nSection 2.4.3 \n Elimination of redundant language \nAttachment C \n Removed and updated all cross-references. Incorporated into \nthe Transmission Congestion Contracts Manual \nAttachment D \n Corrected footnote cross-references \n3.0 06/30/2017 Updates to conform with several tariff changes made between \nJanuary 2013 through August 2016, including: \n Class Year process changes limits and rules re. Commercial \nOperation Dates (tariff changes effective February 2013) \n Threshold for material capacity (ERIS) increases requiring \ninterconnection studies (tariff changes effective February \n2014) \n FERC Order 792 changes re. Small Generator Interconnection \nProcedures (tariff changes effective December 2014 \n Generator outage states, e.g., rules for retired and mothballed \ngenerating facilities (tariff changes effective May 2015) \n Proposed Transmission Interconnection Procedures and \nchanges to the NYISO Transmission Expansion process (tariff \nchanges effective April 1, 2016, FERC order pending) \n BTM:NG filing (interconnection process-related tariff changes \neffective May 19, 2016) \n\nDRAFT PURPOSES ONLY Transmission Expansion and Interconnection Manual | vii\n\n Class Year regulatory milestone changes (tariff changes effective July 5, 2016)  Class Year regulatory milestone changes (tariff changes effective February 22, 2017) Additional updates and revisions, including:  Global update of references (e.g., applicable NERC, NPCC and NYSRC reliability standards)  Added review process for determining whether an SIS is required for proposed NYTO LTP or NYPA TP projects  Global update of NYISO contact information  Added details re. Minimum Interconnection Standard and Deliverability Interconnection Standard methodologies  Added information regarding inter-ISO/RTO interconnection procedures  Added information re. ways to request and obtain CRIS  Other lesser, ministerial changes\n\n4.0 Mm/dd/yyyy\n\nUpdates to reflect revisions made as part of the 2017 \ncomprehensive queue reform, as applicable \n• Increased Efficiencies in the Interconnection Process \n Reduced the number of study agreements \n Created deadlines for study reports to proceed \nthrough stakeholder process \n Clarified roles and responsibilities of parties in the \ninterconnection process \n Made Feasibility S",
